parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended airbag deployment can cause injuries to the driver and passengers, and may lead to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: Airbag deploys without warning
airbag deploys in the absence of a crash
airbag deploys at low speeds
airbag deploys while the vehicle is stationary.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of a crash can increase the risk of injury or fatality to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Airbag does not deploy in a crash
airbag only partially deploys
airbag does not inflate properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunction of the airbag system can cause the airbag to deploy unnecessarily, or fail to deploy in the event of a crash, which can lead to injuries or accidents.
symptoms: SRS light comes on
airbag crash sensor failure
false deployment of airbag
airbag system malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, especially when the vehicle is unable to stop or slow down.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
often when coming to a stop or starting from a standstill
the brakes are unresponsive or fail to engage
the vehicle surges forward without input from the driver.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty brake system can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes are unresponsive or fail to engage
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle pulls to one side when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power and stall, which can lead to accidents, especially if it occurs at high speeds. The loss of power can also make it difficult to control the vehicle, increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls while driving
the engine shuts off without warning
the vehicle is unable to restart immediately
the vehicle takes time to restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An engine fire can cause significant damage to the vehicle and potentially spread to other parts of the vehicle, putting the occupants at risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The vehicle starts smoking
the engine catches on fire
the vehicle is engulfed in flames
the vehicle is damaged beyond repair.
